I mean, whether they're onset of CRS, you know, their side effect profile, outpatient versus inpatient, they're completely different.

00:04:18.380 --> 00:04:21.300
You cannot just say, yep, this is how I'm going to do it for every patient.

00:04:21.300 --> 00:04:24.300
You need to understand the nuances with these drugs, right?

00:04:24.300 --> 00:04:26.120
And then a management plan.

00:04:26.120 --> 00:04:29.040
You've got to have a concise management plan.

00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:35.800
You have to have a plan for the team and a plan for the caregiver and the patient, as well as a checklist before you start a patient.

