00:04:42.420 --> 00:04:54.880
The ERs, the hospital systems, even if you're doing these patients outpatient, they still have to be able to get into the hospital should they have an event, neutropenic fever, whatever that is, as well as knowing where your meds are, right?

00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:59.000
You know, Tostelizumab, Rarity and Anakinra, which fortunately,

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:04.620
we don't have to use much with bispecifics, but you have to know where these meds are and how to get to them when you need them.

